  "prompt": "What is the meaning of tax rebate? As per the year budget, tax rebate is now 5000 for salary more than 5 lakh. What does it mean in a lay man language?",
  "response": "A tax rebate is a reduction in the amount of tax you owe to the government. In simple terms, it means that if you have paid too much in taxes, you can get some of that money back.\n\nIn the context you've mentioned, if the government's budget states that there is a tax rebate of 5,000 rupees for individuals who earn more than 5 lakh rupees a year, it means that if your salary is over 5 lakh rupees, you can reduce your tax bill by 5,000 rupees. \n\nFor example, if your total tax owed is 30,000 rupees, with the rebate of 5,000 rupees, you would only have to pay 25,000 rupees in taxes. Essentially, it's a way to lessen your tax burden if you're earning a certain amount.",
